text: Carl Georg Graff-Wang (18 April 1943 - 18 December 2007) was a Norwegian handball player who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics. He was born in Trondheim and represented the club SK Arild. In 1972 he was part of the Norwegian team which finished ninth in the Olympic tournament. He played four matches and scored five goals. He died in December 2007 in Oslo. ==References== Category:1943 births Category:2007 deaths Category:Norwegian male handball players Category:Olympic handball players of Norway Category:Handball players at the 1972 Summer Olympics
